author: CNN
description: Democratic and Republican leaders speak to the press to discuss a meeting with President Trump ahead of the government funding deadline. President Trump and congressional Republicans believe there is only one way to avert a shutdown at midnight on Tuesday: Senate Democratic Leader Chuck Schumer has to change his mind. GOP leaders still need critical votes from Schumer and his party to sign any funding bill into law. And for now, neither side is backing down. #CNN #News
title: Hear lawmakers' comments after Trump last-chance meeting to stave off shutdown

author: CNN
description: CNN Senior International Correspondent Ben Wedeman spoke to Swedish activist Greta Thunberg while she's en route to Gaza as part of a flotilla intent on delivering things like food and baby formula to the region despite the risks. The Israel Foreign Ministry warned that "necessary measures" would be used to stop aid delivered this way.
title: Greta Thunberg gives update from Gaza-bound flotilla

author: CNN
description:
President Donald Trump said he is “close” to a peace agreement that would end the war in Gaza following his meeting with Israeli Prime Minister Benjamin Netanyahu. The agreement — which Hamas has not yet agreed to — includes the release of all the hostages and the demilitarization of Gaza.

CNN chief White House correspondent Kaitlan Collins reports from the White House, and CNN correspondent Jeremy Diamond reports from Jerusalem. #CNN #News
title: Trump, Netanyahu speak after meeting on Gaza ceasefire proposal

author: CNN
description: Jong Suk, a seasoned window washer, expertly cleans the 125 floors of Seoul's Lotte World Tower, showcasing his skills developed since childhood. CNN's Mike Valerio joins him for a shift to learn more. #cnn #travel #seoul #seoullife #southkorea #southkoreatravel
title: Seoul's coolest window washer cleans Lotte world tower

author: CNN
description: Four people were killed and eight others injured in an attack on a Church of Jesus Christ of Latter-day Saints chapel in Michigan, police said. FBI special agent Reuben Coleman says the FBI is investigating the attack as a targeted act of violence, but declined to give any new details about the shooter's motive.
title: FBI searches for a motive behind MI church attack

author: CNN
description: President Donald Trump said he is “close” to a peace agreement that would end the war in Gaza following his meeting with Israeli Prime Minister Benjamin Netanyahu. The agreement, which Hamas has not yet agreed to, includes the release of all the hostages and the demilitarization of Gaza. During a press conference, Netanyahu said Israel will take matters into its own hands if Hamas doesn't agree to the deal.
title: Netanyahu says 'Israel will finish the job' if Hamas rejects Trump's deal

author: CNN
description:
Michigan's governor and law enforcement officials provided an update on the attack on the Church of Jesus Christ of Latter-Day Saints in Grand Blanc Township, Michigan. All the missing have been accounted for, police said Monday. Four people were killed and eight others injured in the attack during a Sunday morning service, police said. Some of the injured were shot, while others suffered from smoke inhalation, a doctor at a hospital where many were treated said in a Monday news conference.

title: Officials give update on deadly Michigan church attack

author: CNN
description: As New York City Mayor Eric Adams ends his reelection bid, CNN's chief data analyst Harry Enten runs the numbers with John Berman on what this could mean for November's election. #CNN #News
title: Harry Enten breaks down the current odds for the NYC mayoral race

author: CNN
description:
Chile's Atacama Desert, the driest non-polar desert in the world, has burst into bloom this year. It's a phenomenon known as "El Desierto Florido,” or the flowering desert.
#cnn #news
title: The driest desert on Earth is blooming

author: CNN
description:
The Supreme Court is set to vote on whether to consider Ghislaine Maxwell's appeal to overturn her federal sex trafficking conviction. The court is also considering an appeal from President Trump related to his executive order that would end birthright citizenship in the US.

Wolf Blitzer discusses recent developments with CNN chief Supreme Court analyst Joan Biskupic and CNN legal analyst Carrie Cordero. #CNN #News
title: Supreme Court meets today to discuss Ghislaine Maxwell case

author: CNN
description:
A man in a red car drove through a barricade near where a gunman a day earlier rammed his pickup truck into a church, opened fire on congregants and then set the church ablaze.

#CNN #News #Michigan
title: Man drives through barricade day after Michigan church shooting

author: CNN
description: Rory McIlroy and Team Europe were subjected to intense boos and jeers from American fans at the Ryder Cup. After the Europeans held off Team USA, McIlroy spoke about how he handled the heckling at the tournament. #cnn #news #sports #rydercup
title: Rory McIlroy responds to heckling at Ryder Cup

author: CNN
description:
A man in a red car drove through a barricade near where a gunman a day earlier rammed his pickup truck into a church, opened fire on congregants and then set the church ablaze.  At least four people were killed and eight others wounded in the attack during a Sunday morning service.

CNN correspondent Leigh Waldman reports from Grand Blanc, and Wolf Blitzer speaks with former Ferguson, Missouri police chief Jason Armstrong about security threats to worshipers. #CNN #News
title: Man drives through barricade near Michigan church day after shooting

author: CNN
description: CNN's Christiane Amanpour talks to two-time Academy Award-winning actress and activist, Jane Fonda, about finding acting roles later in her career. #CNN #news
title: Jane Fonda gets candid about acting in her 80’s

author: CNN
description: Kate Bolduan talks with CNN senior reporter Matt Egan about the stock ownership boom and its ramifications. #CNN #News
title: Record stock ownership could mean bad news for personal finances

author: CNN
description: Thousands of people marched in Buenos Aires on Saturday after two young women and a fifteen-year old girl were murdered. Their killing, which was livestreamed on social media, has sparked outrage in Argentina.
title: Family of murder victims march in Argentina

author: CNN
description: President Trump may deploy the National Guard to Portland, Oregon. CNN chief data analyst Harry Enten runs the numbers on how popular that move may be. CNN's Sara Sidner also speaks with Rep. Brad Schneider (D-IL) about the possibility of federal troops in Chicago, the possible government shutdown, and President Trump's Gaza peace plan. #CNN #News
title: What do Americans think of ICE? Harry Enten looks at polling

author: CNN
description: Havaianas, the Brazilian brand behind some of the world’s most famous flip flops, has teamed up with German startup Zellerfeld to launch what they're calling the first-ever 3D-printed flip flop. Unlike traditional sandals made from foam and rubber, the new design is printed in one seamless piece — no glue, no stitching — and is fully recyclable.
title: Can you print a flip flop?

author: CNN
description: CNN's Kate Bolduan speaks with Rep. Eric Swalwell (D-CA) about James Comey's indictment and the approaching deadline to avert a government shutdown. #CNN #News
title: Dems, Republicans at stalemate over funding as shutdown looms

author: CNN
description: The country music legend, Dolly Parton, announced that her Las Vegas residency at the Colosseum at Caesars Palace, which was set to begin in December, has been postponed to September 2026 due to health reasons. #CNN #news
title: Dolly Parton postpones Las Vegas shows

author: CNN
description: Young people took to the streets in Peru on Saturday in another round of protests against President Dina Boluarte. The unrest was triggered by a reform to pension laws, but economic instability, corruption and rising crime are also causing concern. #cnn #peru #boluarte
title: Gen Z protesters clash with police in Peru

author: CNN
description: Bad Bunny, who recently wrapped a residency in Puerto Rico, was announced as the Super Bowl LX halftime show performer on Sunday. The Super Bowl XL is set for February 8, 2026 at Levi’s Stadium in Santa Clara, California. #cnn #news #badbunny #superbowl
title: Bad Bunny will headline Super Bowl LX halftime show

author: CNN
description: New York City Mayor Eric Adams is ending his reelection bid, a move long sought by rivals of Democratic nominee Zohran Mamdani who have wanted to consolidate the opposition against him. CNN’s Gloria Pazmino reports. #CNN #News
title: New York City Mayor Eric Adams ends his reelection bid

author: CNN
description: Russia launched over 600 drones and missiles across Ukraine early Sunday in one of the war’s largest attacks. At least four people were killed in Kyiv, with dozens injured in the capital and surrounding areas and at least 30 in Zaporizhzhia. Ukrainian forces continued intercepting drones over Kyiv Sunday morning. CNN's Jessica Dean speaks with former CNN Moscow bureau chief, Jill Dougherty about the situation.   #CNN #News
title: Russia launches massive airstrike on Ukraine, killing 4 and wounding dozens
